{"title":"Ducktrain may be first bike trailer that doesn’t actually attach to the bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/08/ducktrain-self-driving-trailer/","date":1631112473000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"477\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170100/111-800x477.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"droid drive ducktrain\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270785\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>That’s right; a German startup called DroidDrive is in the process of engineering a small trailer that can follow a bike without being physically attached to it. The semi-automated LiDAR-detecting trailer is called Ducktrain (be honest, you think the concept is cute) and it’s currently in the prototype phase.</p><p>In a Ducktrain setup, the trailer communicates with the “tow” vehicle, which can be anything from a bike to a small car. Then, it simply follows the leader. As the name suggests, a train can include multiple Ducks — up to five, the company says.</p><p>The exact release and model details aren’t yet known, so it’s hard to tell how Ducks will impact the consumer market. Currently, the company focuses most of its attention on the platform’s utility for urban deliveries and drop-offs. It posits Ducktrain as a solution for cities where truck delivery is cumbersome and/or prohibited.</p><div id=\"attachment_270791\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270791\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x517/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"droid drive ducktrain\" width=\"1200\" height=\"795\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-297x197.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-800x530.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-768x509.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x517/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.46405460872536963\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-297x197.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-800x530.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07170545/Ducktrain_Alley1-768x509.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270791\">Ducktrain testing in the Kersenmarkt district, Maastricht, Netherlands. Photo: DroidDrive GmbH</p></div><p>“Ducktrain is the answer to the question that many logistics companies ask themselves: how should they deal with the fact that less and less truck traffic is permitted in cities, but at the same time the need to bring goods into the city center is increasing?” said Markus Werle, DroidDrive Co-Founder and CTO.</p><div id=\"attachment_270788\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270788\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1.jpg\" alt=\"droid drive ducktrain\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165522/ducktrain-teamfoto1-768x512.jpg 768w\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270788\">The Ducktrain team. Photo: DroidDrive GmbH</p></div><h2>State of the Ducktrain Self-Driving Trailer Project</h2><p>So far, no real-world video of Ducktrain’s self-propelled production version exists. The live-action teaser video shows a bike towing a Duck traditionally.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZSkBl_dH52w?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>It looks like an efficient system; a single <a href=\"https://ducktrain.io/media/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Duck</a> is only one meter wide, which means it can fit in standard bike lanes. Despite its diminutive size, it can carry payloads up to 661 lbs. in a space big enough for a European standard pallet. Don’t expect to race traffic if you’re towing one; the top speed is a modest 19 mph.</p><div id=\"attachment_270789\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270789\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1.jpg\" alt=\"droid drive ducktrain fits standard Euro pallet\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1.jpg 2560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-2048x1536.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1.jpg 2560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165728/Duck_Back-scaled-1-2048x1536.jpg 2048w\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270789\">A Duck, loaded for scale. Photo: DroidDrive GmbH</p></div><p>All existing information from the company points specifically toward commercial use, so it’s unclear whether Ducktrain will take off for individual consumers, or as a taxi system. For now, DroidDrive focuses on last-mile food, parcel, and general delivery uses.</p><div id=\"attachment_270787\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270787\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1.jpg\" alt=\"autonomous trailers that fit in bike lanes\" width=\"1200\" height=\"819\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-297x203.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-800x546.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-120x82.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-768x524.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-297x203.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-800x546.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-120x82.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07165415/Ducktrain_BicycleLane1-768x524.jpg 768w\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270787\">Render: DroidDrive GmbH</p></div><h2>Assessing Availability and MSRP</h2><p>Measuring the expense of Ducktrain against the costs of commercial delivery is one thing, but assessing it for <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/06/24/danny-macaskill-archive-the-6-month-barrel-roll-with-trailer-progression/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">personal needs</a> may be quite another. Though the company hasn’t stated an MSRP yet, one outlet reported that <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/urban-transport/trailerduck-ducktrain-bicycle-trailer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">renting a Duck could cost $587 per month</a>. But if you’re curious, <a href=\"https://ducktrain.io/#contact\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">DroidDrive is taking inquiries and pre-orders</a>. Delivery starts in late 2022.</p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Sam Anderson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d7966540318168877cd9eb4d9e600e7b0b4bb0156c995cdd0de426cd5338192a","category":"Cycling"}